cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is about Grammatical Error Correction (GEC) task, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes two data synthesis methods, which involve machine learning techniques such as Sequence to Sequence framework and error generation models. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves experiments and performance evaluation, which may suggest it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories.
